.TH RUFUSARM64-NONBOOTABLE-FORMAT 1 "20 July 2026" "RufusArm64 0.13.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
rufusarm64-nonbootable-format \- erase and format a removable drive as data-only media
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B rufusarm64-nonbootable-format
.B --device
.I /dev/DEVICE
.B --dry-run
.RI [ options ]
.br
.B sudo rufusarm64-nonbootable-format
.B --device
.I /dev/DEVICE
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B rufusarm64-nonbootable-format
is the dedicated identity-bound data-only formatter. It erases one explicitly
selected whole block device, writes one GPT or MBR partition, creates FAT32,
exFAT, NTFS, or ext4, and verifies the published partition table, kernel
geometry, filesystem type, label, and read-only checker result. The result is
not claimed bootable.
.PP
The unprivileged dry run resolves the current kernel device, checks the selected
identity, exact capacity and logical sector size, validates the requested label,
and calculates complete aligned geometry before authentication. Destructive
execution reconstructs and revalidates the same canonical plan immediately
before erasure.
.SH LAYOUT
Exactly one data partition is created with a 1 MiB aligned start and a 1 MiB
reserved tail. GPT uses Microsoft basic-data for FAT32, exFAT, and NTFS and the
Linux filesystem-data type for ext4. MBR uses type 0x0c for FAT32, 0x07 for
exFAT/NTFS, and 0x83 for ext4. Geometry beyond the exact MBR address range is
refused with instructions to use GPT.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI --device " /dev/DEVICE"
Select the exact whole target disk. Partitions, non-block paths, the running
system disk, protected devices, and unsupported virtual targets are refused.
.TP
.BI --expected-identity " TOKEN"
Require the current token from
.BR "rufusarm64-cli list --json" .
Mandatory with noninteractive or override-capable terminal modes.
.TP
.BI --scheme " gpt|mbr"
Choose GPT or MBR. GPT is the default.
.TP
.BI --filesystem " fat32|exfat|ntfs|ext4"
Choose the data filesystem. FAT32 is the default.
.TP
.BI --label " LABEL"
Set a label under the selected filesystem's validated length and character
contract.
.TP
.B --dry-run
Print the complete non-destructive plan without opening the target for writing.
.TP
.B --json
Emit one deterministic JSON plan or final report.
.TP
.B --yes
Skip terminal confirmation. Accepted only with an exact expected identity.
.TP
.B --allow-fixed
Permit an explicitly selected non-removable whole disk for direct terminal use.
The graphical path does not expose this option and protected-device refusals
remain active.
.TP
.B --no-unmount
Refuse mounted descendants instead of guarded unmounting. The graphical path
does not expose this option.
.TP
.BI --cancel-file " PATH"
Use the owner-private graphical cancellation marker beneath `/run/user`.
.TP
.BR --version , " -v"
Print the installed version.
.SH CONFIRMATION
Interactive terminal execution requires the exact generated phrase:
.PP
.nf
FORMAT /dev/DEVICE AS FILESYSTEM USING SCHEME LABEL LABEL
.fi
.PP
An empty label uses `WITHOUT A LABEL`. A mismatch stops before the target is
opened for formatting.
.SH FAILURE AND CANCELLATION
Cancellation before erasure reports that the medium was unchanged. Once an
erase command is invoked, cancellation or failure conservatively reports the
medium changed and non-reusable until a complete format succeeds. Do not remove
the drive while an operation is active.
.SH POLKIT BOUNDARY
The installed graphical action executes only the package-private formatter with
noninteractive JSON, exact identity, owner-private cancellation, normal
removable-media policy, and guarded unmounting. Fixed-disk and no-unmount
overrides are terminal-only.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR rufusarm64 (1),
.BR rufusarm64-cli (1),
.BR rufusarm64-device-backup (1),
.BR rufusarm64-device-qualify (1)
